megawatt-hour were a Canadian public utility, a subsidiary of San Diego Gas =
&=20
Electric's parent company, and the Los Angeles Department of Water and Power=
,=20
the report shows. Their average prices ranged from $498 a megawatt-hour=20
charged by Powerex, the trading arm of British Columbia's BC Hydro, to $292=20
an hour by the DWP.=20
