generators who wear cowboy hats," he said. "Their profits were 100% to 400%=20
above last year. . . . Just because there are other entities who are chargin=
g=20
us more [per megawatt-hour] doesn't change the fact that we are getting=20
ripped off by companies from Houston, Tulsa, Atlanta or Charlotte."=20
