those of the biggest private companies. For example, Houston-based Enron, on=
e=20
of the nation's biggest power traders, charged an average of $181 per=20
megawatt-hour. And Atlanta-based Mirant, which sold the most to the state, a=
=20
total of $706 million, charged an average of $225 per megawatt-hour.=20
