said late Monday the company was unable to comment because it had yet to see=
=20
the figures released by the state. Officials at DWP, who could not be reache=
d=20
Monday evening, have defended their pricing, saying the costs of producing=20
the power needed by the state were extremely high.=20
More Power Bought Than Projected=20
